Citation.sTitle: Volumetric and viscometric properties of binary mixtures of {methyl tert-butyl  ether (MTBE) + alcohol} at several temperatures and p = 0.1 MPa: Experimental  results and application of the ERAS model
Citation.sAbstract: Densities and viscosities of binary mixtures of {methyl tert-butyl ether (MTBE) + methanol, or +ethanol,  or +1-propanol, or +2-propanol, or +1-butanol, or +1-pentanol, or +1-hexanol} have been determined as a function of composition at several temperatures and atmospheric pressure. The temperatures studied were (293.15, 298.15, 303.15, and 308.15) K. The experimental results have been used to calculate the excess molar volume and viscosity deviation. Both excess molar volume and viscosity deviation values were negative over the entire range of mole fraction for all temperatures and systems studied. Moreover, the excess molar volume values have  been used to test the applicability of the Extended Real Associated Solution (ERAS) model.
